#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:99
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Reverse ({mod}R)\n"
"Reverse the direction of all relationship paths shown, computing the "
"relationship from the other person's perspective. Click again to restore "
"the original path."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:111
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Copy results ({mod}C)\n"
"Copy the entire contents of the results pane to the clipboard. When the "
"results text area has keyboard focus, {mod}C copies only the selected "
"text as usual."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:119
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Save ({mod}S)\n"
"Save the results to a text file."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:124
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Find ({mod}F)\n"
"Type to filter the list of people. Search by any name variation. Use the "
"filter box to search by other information in a person's GEDCOM record, "
"such as geographic location. Press Enter to jump directly to the first "
"match. Use the checkboxes to show only people matching tags, allow fuzzy "
"name matching, or include married names."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:135
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Find Nearest Matches ({mod}N)\n"
"Find the closest tagged matches to the selected person. The results are "
"ranked by proximity to the selected person, with ties broken by the "
"number of tags (if any) associated with the match. Use the 'Results' and "
"'Max Depth' settings to adjust how many results are returned and how far "
"to search within the tree.\n"
"\n"
"Also triggered by pressing Enter when selecting a person."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:147
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Filter ({mod}I)\n"
"Type to filter the list of people by any information in their GEDCOM "
"record, such as geographic location. This filter is applied in addition "
"to the Find box above."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:153
msgid ""
"Enter a keyword to filter the list of tags used for finding relationship "
"paths. Leave this blank to use only the page marker keyword to find "
"relationship paths."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:157
msgid ""
"Enter a unique keyword to use as a page marker when finding relationship "
"paths. Leave this blank to use only the tag keyword to find relationship "
"paths."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:163
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Set Home Person ({mod}H)\n"
"Set the selected person as the home person for finding relationship paths."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:167
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Profile ({mod}E)\n"
"View the full GEDCOM record for the selected person, along with a summary"
" of biographical and family information. Shift-Click for Tree View."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:171
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Tree View ({mod}E)\n"
"Open the family tree view for the selected person. Shift-Click for "
"Profile View."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:175
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Select Tag for Finding Paths ({mod}T)\n"
"Select a new tag for finding the path between the selected person and the"
" closest people with that tag."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:179
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Find Relationship Paths ({mod}P)\n"
"Find multiple paths between the selected person and any other person in "
"your tree. Select any person in the results to find the relationships "
"between the originally selected person and the newly-selected person."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:182
msgid ""
"Number of Results\n"
"Specify how many results to return when finding the closest people who "
"are tagged as well as the number of paths between the selected person and"
" the home person."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:188
msgid ""
"Maximum Depth For Finding Relationships\n"
"Specify how far to search within the tree for tagged matches and "
"relationship paths between two people. Higher values will find more "
"distant connections but will take longer to find in large trees. "
"Reasonable values are 10 for fast searching or 50 to find very distant "
"but often interesting paths between people in your tree. To change this "
"setting permanently, alter it in the preferences window."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:198
msgid ""
"Fuzzy Threshold\n"
"Similarity cutoff for fuzzy name search, from 0.00 to 1.00. Lower values "
"allow more matches; higher values are stricter."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:203
msgid ""
"Maximum Search Results\n"
"Maximum number of people shown in the search results list. Higher values "
"may slow down filtering in very large trees."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:210
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Toggle Tagged Only ({mod}D)\n"
"When checked, only people flagged as tagged will be shown in search "
"results. Default Tags are DNA-related, but you can set other tag terms. "
"Default is unchecked to show all people, but checking this focusses on "
"tagged matches in large trees."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:214
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Toggle Fuzzy Search ({mod}U)\n"
"Allow fuzzy name matching in search results. Fuzzy matching uses a "
"similarity ratio to find names similar to the search term, which can help"
" find matches when names are misspelled or have minor variations."
msgstr ""

#: C:/apps/src/gedcom-navigator/src/gedcom_strings.py:218
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Toggle Married Names ({mod}M)\n"
"Include women's married names in Find searches by combining each woman's "
"given name with the last names of her husbands."
msgstr ""

